def binary_search(nums, target):
    left, right = 0, len(nums) - 1
    while left <= right:
        mid = left + (right - left) // 2
        if nums[mid] == target:
            return mid
        elif nums[mid] < target:
            left = mid + 1
        else:
            right = mid - 1
    return -1

The loop uses left < right because we are shrinking the search space until both pointers meet at the boundary.

