def find_leftmost(nums, target):
    left, right = 0, len(nums)
    while left < right:
        mid = left + (right - left) // 2
        if nums[mid] < target:
            left = mid + 1
        else:
            right = mid
    return left

The loop stops when left == right, meaning the smallest valid position for the target has been found.

The midpoint is calculated as mid = (left + right + 1) // 2 to bias the midpoint to the right side.

